Miss Beauty Etsanyi Tukura is one of the housemates of the Big Brother Naija Season 7. Beauty represented Taraba State in the 2019 Miss Nigeria beauty pageant. She was announced among the 18 finalists at the grand finale of the 43rd edition of the beauty pageant at the Eko Convention Centre, Lagos. Beauty received a luxurious apartment and a car as part of the gifts for winning the pageant.    Economy quakes under biting inflation     Business, consumers groan as inflation wreaks havoc     How CBN is fighting inflation   1. Beauty was born in Port Harcourt, her family moved to Lagos when she was 2. 2. She is the last child from a family of six. 3. She went to American University of Nigeria Academy in Yola (Adamawa State) for her senior secondary education. 4. Beauty studied Law at the Afe Babalola University, Ado- Ekiti (Ekiti State). 5. She won her first pageant when she was in elementary school. Beauty has also contested in two major pageants – Most Beautiful Girl Taraba 2015 which she won and reigned until 2017, and she was the 43rd Miss Nigeria. 6. According to her, she sees herself as a feminist. 7. Beauty’s dream is to empower young girls to be the best version of themselves.